Códigos

🖥

library(plot3D)
library(plotly)

Gráfica lineal

M <- mesh(seq(-1, 6*pi, length.out = 50),seq(0, pi, length.out = 50))
x <- M$x
y <- M$y

alpha_1 <- 0.25
alpha_2 <- 0.75

z <- alpha_1 * x +  alpha_2 * y

#surf3D(x, y, z, colvar = z, colkey = TRUE, 
#       box = TRUE, bty = "b", phi = 20, theta = 120)

fig <- plot_ly(x = x, y = y, z = z) %>% add_surface()

fig

Gráfica Cobb-Douglas

M <- mesh(seq(0.01, pi, length.out = 50),seq(0.01, pi, length.out = 50))
x <- M$x
y <- M$y

A <- 1
alpha_1 <- 0.5
alpha_2 <- 0.5

z <- A *  x ^ alpha_1 * y ^ alpha_2

fig <- plot_ly(x = x, y = y, z = z) %>% add_surface()

fig

Gráfica de Leontief

M <- mesh(seq(0, 10, length.out = 50),seq(0.0, 10, length.out = 50))
x <- M$x
y <- M$y

alpha_1 <- 1
alpha_2 <- 1

z <- pmin(alpha_1 * x, alpha_2 * y)

fig <- plot_ly(x = x, y = y, z = z) %>% add_surface()

fig

Gráfica de elasticidad constante de sustitución

M <- mesh(seq(0, 10, length.out = 50),seq(0.0, 10, length.out = 50))
x <- M$x
y <- M$y

A <- 1
alpha_1 <- 1
alpha_2 <- 1
rho <- 0.5

z <- A * (alpha_1 * x ^ (-rho) + alpha_2 * y ^ (-rho)) ^ (-1/rho)

fig <- plot_ly(x = x, y = y, z = z) %>% add_surface()

fig
